      "raw_text": "Assistant City Engineer Mcintyre were\npresent with draft of the plans.\n\n\nAn understanding having been prev\niously arrived at, Commissioners Collin\nand Butler voted to issue ten $500 war\nrants to the order of w. II. Acuff, the\naccredited representative of the cham\nDer of commerce committee, to which\nhas been given the task of fitting out\nproper exhibit from the Inland EN-\npire to the st. Louis exposition next\nyear. These warrants are not to bear\ninterest, and represent the county\nshare, while the city is to give $4,000.\n\n\nThe commissioners appointed j. j.\nGholson constable in Stevens precinct,\nvacancy having occurred. The resig-\nnation of Henry Ravens as road super\nvisor in the Latah district was re-\nceived."
    }
